<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.238.116767.figure2>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Ophiorrhiza reflexa A, B habit C stipule D young inflorescence E inflorescence in lateral view F inflorescences in different development stages G bracts from lower part to upper part of inflorescence H leaves I corollas in lateral view J corollas in top view K longitudinally dissected long-styled flower L longitudinally dissected short-styled flower M infructescence. Photos by L. Wu. Scale bars: 3 mm (C); 1 cm (G, J-L); 2 cm (E, F, I, M); 10 cm (H)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/992267" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.238.116767.figure3>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Morphological comparison of Ophiorrhiza alatiflora and O. japonica A-H O. alatiflora A habit B inflorescences in different developmental stages C calyces and corollas in lateral view D corollas in top view E inflorescence F young inflorescence G longitudinally dissected long-styled flower H longitudinally dissected short-styled flower I-M O. japonica I habit J corollas in lateral view K corollas in top view L, M young inflorescence. Photos by L. Wu. Scale bars: 1 cm (C-H, J-M); 2 cm (B)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/992268" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.238.116767.figure4>
